Finished up my ‘54 pre unit a couple days ago just in time for @paradiseroadshow! This thing was super fun and also a giant learning experience to build. I can’t thank my best bud @macspeedcycles for his endless knowledge and guidance throughout this whole project! I barely knew how to weld before this thing, and Reid was patient with me and answered all my stupid questions while letting me use his shop while I made the tank, fender, painted, and pieced the whole thing together. Reid also built the motor and trans because I ain’t an engine builder by any means haha. Anyways, I’m super hyped on it and super stoked it’s first time out was at @paradiseroadshow! Thanks @adri_law @fevvvvaa @hwy and the whole paradise crew for always putting on a solid show, can’t wait for next year! 

My friend @zachpeacock snagged these sick ass shots of the bike and my beautiful girlfriend over the weekend, thanks so much dude! 🙏🏼 #triumph #triumphchopper #triumphpreunit #paradiseroadshow #teamworkmakesthedreamwork
